CPU Scheduler Simulator
Simulating FCFS, SJF, Priority Scheduling, and Round Robin.
Round Robin quantum: 3

==================== INPUT WORKLOAD ====================
Priority convention: smaller number = higher priority
Deadline rule: missed if completion_time > deadline

Process      Arrival     Burst  Priority  Deadline
--------------------------------------------------
P1                 0         4         1         4
P2                 0         3         2         6
P3                 0         2         3         8
P4                 0         1         4         9


========================================================
FCFS - First Come First Served
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Among available processes, run the earliest arriving process first. Ties use input order.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  4)  P1
  [ 4,  7)  P2
  [ 7,  9)  P3
  [ 9, 10)  P4

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |4 P2 |7 P3 |9 P4 |10

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       4       1         4           0         4         0           4         0       no
P2               0       3       2         6           4         7         4           7         4      yes
P3               0       2       3         8           7         9         7           9         7      yes
P4               0       1       4         9           9        10         9          10         9      yes

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 10
  Total busy time       : 10
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.40 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 5.00
  Average turnaround    : 7.50
  Average response time : 5.00
  Deadline misses       : 3 / 4


========================================================
SJF - Shortest Job First
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Whenever the CPU becomes free, run the available process with the smallest burst time.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  1)  P4
  [ 1,  3)  P3
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6, 10)  P1

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P4 |1 P3 |3 P2 |6 P1 |10

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       4       1         4           6        10         6          10         6      yes
P2               0       3       2         6           3         6         3           6         3       no
P3               0       2       3         8           1         3         1           3         1       no
P4               0       1       4         9           0         1         0           1         0       no

Summary metrics:
