  Total busy time       : 10
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.40 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 2.50
  Average turnaround    : 5.00
  Average response time : 2.50
  Deadline misses       : 1 / 4


========================================================
Priority Scheduling
========================================================
Non-preemptive. Whenever the CPU becomes free, run the available process with the highest priority. Smaller priority number means higher priority.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  4)  P1
  [ 4,  7)  P2
  [ 7,  9)  P3
  [ 9, 10)  P4

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |4 P2 |7 P3 |9 P4 |10

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       4       1         4           0         4         0           4         0       no
P2               0       3       2         6           4         7         4           7         4      yes
P3               0       2       3         8           7         9         7           9         7      yes
P4               0       1       4         9           9        10         9          10         9      yes

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 10
  Total busy time       : 10
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.40 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 5.00
  Average turnaround    : 7.50
  Average response time : 5.00
  Deadline misses       : 3 / 4


========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  P1
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6,  8)  P3
  [ 8,  9)  P4
  [ 9, 10)  P1

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |3 P2 |6 P3 |8 P4 |9 P1 |10

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       4       1         4           0        10         6          10         0      yes
P2               0       3       2         6           3         6         3           6         3       no
P3               0       2       3         8           6         8         6           8         6       no
P4               0       1       4         9           8         9         8           9         8       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 10
  Total busy time       : 10
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.40 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 5.75
  Average turnaround    : 8.25
  Average response time : 4.25
  Deadline misses       : 1 / 4


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served          5.00            7.50          5.00         3      100.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                2.50            5.00          2.50         1      100.00
Priority Scheduling                     5.00            7.50          5.00         3      100.00
Round Robin                             5.75            8.25          4.25         1      100.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
